article.headline: Jeanne-Rose's 24 lead Central Connecticut past Merrimack 75-70
article.description: — Allan Jeanne-Rose scored 24 points as Central Connecticut beat Merrimack 75-70 on Monday night.
article.linkText: Jeanne-Rose's 24 lead Central Connecticut past Merrimack 75-70
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- — Allan Jeanne-Rose scored 24 points as Central Connecticut beat Merrimack 75-70 on Monday night. Jeanne-Rose added eight rebounds for the Blue Devils (9-7, 3-0 Northeast Conference). Jayden Brown scored 15 points, shooting 5 of 9 from the field and 5 for 5 from the line. Kellen Amos had 12 points and shot 4 for 9 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 2 of 3 from the free throw line. Jordan Derkack led the way for the Warriors (9-9, 3-1) with 16 points. Adam Clark added 15 points and eight assists for Merrimack. Bryan Etumnu also recorded 13 points and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
